🎃💕🎉IS IT TOO EARLY FOR PUMPKIN? I think not. Here’s my Vegan Pumpkin Spice Latte!
.
🎉Did you know the PSL at Starbucks isn’t vegan? Unfortunately there’s milk in the syrup.
.
🎃I developed this recipe a couple years ago, and since then hundreds of you have said it’s now a mainstay in your fall rituals. I hope you love it as much as I do.
.
RECIPE
2/3 Cup Brewed Coffee
1 Cup Unsweetened Cashew Milk
2 Tbsp Pumpkin Puree
1/2 Tsp Pumpkin Pie Spice
1 Tbsp maple syrup
.
Add all ingredients to a pot over medium heat. Whisk, and heat until warm.
.
Pour in a mug and enjoy with coconut whipped cream on top if desired.
.

🤯💕🎉Ep 15: SCRAPPY COOKING - vegan cheese ball using almond pulp.
.
🌱For the almond milk:
1 cup raw almonds, soaked overnight
4 cups filtered water
.
🔥For the cheese ball:
1 to 1 1/2 cups almond pulp
1/4 cup nutritional yeast
3 tbsp coconut oil
1 tbsp dried parsley
1 tbsp apple cider vinegar
1/2 teaspoon sea salt
.
✨Blend the almonds and water until a “milk” is formed.
.
🙏Drain using a cheese cloth or leotard and transfer the plant-based milk to a clean container in the fridge (store up to 3 days). You can sweeten it with maple syrup and add a little sea salt as desired.
.
✨Reserve the leftover pulp and ensure it is drained as much as possible. Add the remaining ingredients, stir, taste and adjust as needed. With your hands, roll into a ball and chill in the fridge until ready to eat. This won’t be SUPER cheesy but I makes a delicious repurposed spread.
.

1 cup plant milk of choice
1 avocado (I had one kind of on the edge so I threw it in)
.
Blend, freeze and ENJOY in your favorite smoothies.
.

🍓🤫CHIA JAM that might just help you 💩
.
If you struggle with a ✨slow digestive✨ system, you might want to throw some chia seeds in the mix. This amazing raspberry chia jam comes together in 5 minutes with 3 ingredients (and no added sugar)!
.
2 cups raspberries
Squeeze of fresh lemon juice
2 tbsp chia seeds
.
🤌🏼In a pot over medium heat, add the raspberries, and with a spoon crush until they are “mushy”.
.
Add the lemon juice and chia seeds, and mix until combined.
.
Take off the burner when you have a jam consistency, and allow to set for a few minutes. Transfer to a jar and keep in your fridge for up to a week!
.

🤯💕🔥EP 13 Scrappy Cooking: DRAGON FRUIT SKIN JELLY
.
🤌🏼So many of you sent me the original video for this dragon fruit jelly by makanterusss with gelatin. I decided to give it a shot with agar agar, and it WORKS!
.
🤣I’m not sure I’d go through the effort of this one again, especially because dragon fruit has such a neutral flavor, but it sure makes a pretty dessert. I’m going to play around using a fruit juice for a more pungent version.
.
🥰RECIPE:
3 dragon fruits
4 water 
1/2 cup maple syrup 
3 tsp agar agar 
1 cup chopped dragon fruit 
.
Peel the very outer shell of the dragon fruit, then remove the skin in tact and cut into large slices, cleaning out the centers thoroughly and saving for a smoothie or other recipe.
.
Bring a pot of 4 cups of water to a boil, and add the dragon fruit skins.
.
Cook until the color has integrated with the water, then pull out the dragon fruit skin leaving only the liquid behind.
.
Add the maple syrup and agar agar and bring to a boil. 
.
Transfer to a container, and add in your chopped dragon fruit.
.
Place in the freezer for a half hour and enjoy immediately.
. 🌱What scrap do you want to see used next?
.

\
Welcome back to episode 13 of scrappy cooking, where I take common food scraps and turn them into delicious recipes.   So many of you sent me a recipe video of this dragon fruit skin jelly using gelitan, so I decided to try a vegan version with ay-gar ay-gar and I’m so happy to report it worked. I’ll link the original creators video in the caption, but you should really… Stop throwing out dragon fruit skins.  Make dragon fruit jelly instead.

🌱💕🤯SCRAPPY COOKING EPISODE 12: Aquafaba Chocolate Pudding (aka bean water lol)
.
💃You’ve probably heard that aquafaba is a magical transforming liquid, but how do you actually make that happen? The key is a good hand mixer and patience. After around 10 minutes, it will turn into a foamy white “meringue” just like egg whites - and you can’t over whip it!
.
🤩You can use aquafaba for:
- A vegan egg replacement in baking (unwrapped)
- Vegan meringues
- This chocolate pudding or a mousse… and more!
.
👌Here’s how to make this delicious chocolate pudding: Aquafaba from 1 can of chickpeas
Semi-sweet vegan chocolate chips, melted
1 tbsp sugar of choice (optional)
.
👏Drain you can of chickpeas, and set them aside for another recipe (like my chickpea smashed sandwich), capturing the aquafaba in a large bowl.
.
🤩Now, melt your chocolate however you would like. I used the microwave, but you can use the double broiler method. You can add a bit of almond milk to help it achieve a velvety consistency.
.
🔥Using a hand mixer, or if you’re brave, a handheld whisk, and beat until you achieve stiff white peaks in your “meringue”. This will take around 10 minutes so be patient. You can’t over whip aquafaba.
.
🍫Once the chocolate sauce has cooled, incorporate it into the meringue, along with the sugar if using. Gently stir until it becomes chocolatey goodness. It’s normal for the meringue to lose some of its foaminess and size here.
.
🤌🏼Transfer to jars and allow to cool in the fridge for a few hours before enjoying as you would pudding or chocolate mousse!
.

🍓🥰💕EP 11 SCRAPPY COOKING: STRAWBERRY TOP VINEGAR.
.
💃Did you know you can eat strawberry tops? If you’re not throwing them in your smoothie - try making this strawberry infused vinegar. Add your tops to any white vinegar for a few days, and you’ll have a bright red sweet vinegar perfect for salads, or even added to drinks!
.
1/2 cup strawberry tops
White vinegar of choice
.
Pour vinegar and strawberry tops in a sealable jar. Allow to rest at room temperature for at least 2 days. Transfer mixture to a sealable bottle, discarding the tops. Use as you would regular vinegar!
.

🤯🔥💕BUFFALO TOFU SKEWERS featuring @primalkitchenfoods unbelievable no dairy Buffalo Sauce with cashew butter.
.
🙌🏻This creamy, deliriously good buffalo sauce is perfect for marinating tofu, or as a dipping sauce. Find it across Costco locations in the southeast.
.
🥰RECIPE:
 .
1 block extra firm tofu, pressed, torn into equal sized pieces
1 cup @primalkitchenfoods buffalo sauce
.
 
Add all ingredients to a container, and mix until the tofu is well coated in the sauce. Place in the fridge to marinate for at least one hour.
.
After removing from the fridge, stack the buffalo tofu onto skewers of choice. Place on a BBQ heated at 450F, and grill for approximately 5 minutes on each side, until the tofu is slightly crisped on the outside. Enjoy over rice or with a salad.
.
You can also bake this recipe. Simple place in the oven at 400F for about half an hour, turning halfway through.
.

🥦💕🤯Ep 10 SCRAPPY COOKING: Broccoli stem FRIES
.
💰Broccoli isn’t cheap - and the stems are one of the most delicious + nutritious parts. So STOP throwing them out. You can chop em’ up and stir fry just like the florets, or make them into these delicious broccoli stem fries. They’re kind of reminiscent of asparagus.
.
💃VEGAN RECIPE
2 broccoli stems, peeled, washed and cut into fry shapes
Cornstarch or arrowroot to toss
1 cup almond milk with 1 tbsp lemon juice
1 cup breadcrumbs or panko
.
Preheat the oven to 400F and line a baking sheet with parchment.
.
Toss broccoli stems in cornstarch or arrowroot, then your almond milk and lemon juice mix and finally the bread crumbs. Transfer to a baking sheet.
.
Bake for 15 minutes until crispy. Do not overcook or they will be very stringy.
.

🤯💕☕️DATE SEED COFFEE (Ep 9 of scrappy cooking)!
.
💃Did you know you can turn date seeds into a beverage, reminiscent of coffee without the caffeine? Date seed coffee has a more subtle flavor, but it’s really delicious and gives you a great excuse to keep those date seeds around.
.
RECIPE
1/2 cup date seeds (around 8 seeds per cup)
.
Preheat the oven to 400F and line a baking sheet with parchment.
.
Remove the seeds from your dates. I used the seeds from medjool dates. Clean thoroughly.
.
Roast on a parchment lined baking sheet for around 40 minutes.
.
After removing from the oven, use a coffee grinder or food processor to create date coffee grinds.
.
Prepare how you would regular coffee. You can mix it with your morning coffee as well, to provide a lower caffeine alternative.
.

🤯💕🔥CORN FLAKES. By @plantyou - cereal series requests in the comments please!
.
🎉Welcome to the CEREAL SERIES - where we make healthier homemade versions of your favorite cereals.
.
🤩Today it’s corn flakes: 
.
1 cup cornmeal + 2 tbsp
1 tbsp maple syrup
1 tsp vanilla extract
.
Preheat the oven to 350F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Spray with a small amount of oil to prevent sticking. 
.
Add 1 cup of the cornmeal to a bowl, and slowly pour in 3/4 a cup of water, vanilla extract, a pinch of salt and the maple syrup. Whisk until you achieve a thick smooth consistency, like pancake batter, adding more water as needed.
.
Pour this onto your prepared baking sheet. You want to achieve a layer approximately 1/4 of an inch thick.
.
Add a couple tablespoons of the dried cornmeal on top of the batter for “crunch”
.
Bake for 10 minutes, remove from the oven and break apart. Lower the oven temperature to 300F, and bake for an additional 30 to 40 minutes until crispy. Enjoy with plant-based milk!
.
.
